2005-01-01|2005-12-30.description: Now that Spider-Man knows the identity of Aunt May¹s abductor, what¹s he gonna do about it? Think you know the answer? Guess again. Guest-starring Black Cat.
2005-01-01|2005-12-30.name: The Last Stand, Part 2

2005-01-01|2005-12-30.description: "SATURDAY NIGHT FEVER" concludes as a whole new era for the Marvel Universe begins! Excalibur’s mission is called into doubt when the truth about one of their members is revealed to the citizens of Genosha!
2005-01-01|2005-12-30.name: Casting Fate!

2005-01-01|2005-12-30.description:
TOO MUCH INFOMATION (PART 1 OF 2) David Alleyne, a.k.a. PRODIGY of the New Mutants, can absorb the skills and knowledge of anyone close by —but is doomed to forget everything as soon as they’re gone. So what would happen if he could keep that knowledge instead of forgetting? He’d be the smartest kid in the world, right? Is it too much of a good thing?

Following another mocking from Julian, David believes that he’s useless if he can’t keep the knowledge he absorbs. After a session with Emma Frost, he finds out that a mental block in his mind prevents him from keeping it. He wants it removed. After a discussion with Dani, David decides to go for it. The plan works and, day after day, David absorbs everything he can: from science knowledge to fighting skills. But his attitude too changes, and not in the good way. Meanwhile, Kevin holds another session with Dr. Sean Garrison, who’s interested to learn more about Laurie after Kevin mentions what her powers are. Later, new Field Day contests are held, and this year the New Mutants win! David also gets a trophy for all-around academic excellence. A few hours later, David announces that the school has got nothing more to offer him and leaves. However, he promises to help Josh find the full potential of his powers. Three months pass. In this time, David creates his very own Alleyne Enterprises and gathers a press conference. Proudly, he announces to have found a cure for both cancer and AIDS! And he did that together with Josh Foley, who agreed to serve as test object. But unfortunately, this caused Josh to… die!
2005-01-01|2005-12-30.name: Too Much Information, Part 1

2005-01-01|2005-12-30.description: The X-Men and the Danger Room entity briefly converse, but it is only allowed by the entity to let them know its only desire: to beat them to death. The battle is ferocious, however the entity is able to use its memory banks from the Danger Room to counter every strategy, as it has seem them all in battle countless times. Eventually, the X-Men fall. Some fall victim to their compassion for their own teammates’ well being, and others to just brute force. As this transpires, Special Agent Brand and her allies at SWORD, notice the destruction at the Institute. An extraterrestrial advisor is able to sense that the events are from a non-human presence, which Brand hopes will deal with their problem for them. After the battle, the entity uses the X-wing to travel to Genosha to complete its self-assigned mission, which is to kill Xavier. Xavier, however, having been in communication with the entity for a short while, tells it that it has miscalculated. While it had already fought the X-Men an untold number of times in both the Danger Room and its mind… it has never fought him!
2005-01-01|2005-12-30.name: Dangerous, Part 4

2005-01-01|2005-12-30.description: All the pieces are in place and all the lies have fallen away. The stage has been set for Nightcrawler's final confrontation with the person who's ripped apart his past. It's a battle to the death, and its outcome could affect not just the world we know, but the dimensions beyond !
2005-01-01|2005-12-30.name: The Winding Way, Part 4: Wicked Things

2005-01-01|2005-12-30.description:
The all-new Scorpion successfully infiltrates Advanced Idea Mechanics but gets more than she bargains for when her first mission for A.I.M. is one of assassination. Is maintaining her cover worth killing for? Also: S.H.I.E.L.D. at last discovers the horrifying secret of the Scorpion's poison touch... but too late to save her!

BONUS: Introducing a new horror sensation to the Marvel Universe—Vampire by Night! Who is this mysterious girl, who in the Marvel U is she related to and what kind of bizarre curse does she possess? Get in on the start with the first part of this new 8-page back-up feature with art by Federica Manfredi.
2005-01-01|2005-12-30.name: Gone Native/Vampire by Night

2005-01-01|2005-12-30.description: Bishop and Ismael travel beneath the streets to uncover the mystery behind "The Worm." All while Ismael’s dangerous addiction might spell disaster for those around him!
2005-01-01|2005-12-30.name: Underground, Part 4

2005-01-01|2005-12-30.description: The Ringmaster faces the combined might of Spider-Man, Moon Knight, and Daredevil--with the fate of the world hanging in the balance. This ultra-climactic issue brings the second thrilling arc of Marvel Team-Up to a close and paves the way for our third titanic story arc starting next month!
2005-01-01|2005-12-30.name: Master Of The Ring, Part 5 & 6

2005-01-01|2005-12-30.description: As a thief, Gambit has faced some risky jobs, but this may be his most dangerous yet—he'll have to infiltrate the heavily-fortified home of the world's most powerful mutants. That's right…Gambit’s got to swipe something right from under the noses of his teammates, the X-Men!
2005-01-01|2005-12-30.name: X, Lies and Videotape

2005-01-01|2005-12-30.description: Shipwrecked in Okinawa, Sarasa has met Doctor Basho, who has healed her eyes, and Shuri, who has fled a coup in Sanyo. Together, they must help stop a plot to kill Okinawa's president and protect the independent nation from invasion!
2005-01-01|2005-12-30.name: Vol. 10

2005-01-01|2005-12-30.description: Rich boy Tsukasa returns to Japan after he discovers the true identity of Tsukushi's "Kinsan." Tsukushi herself is having trouble accepting his identity. Then Kinsan invites Tsukushi to a swank party where they bump into Tsukasa, who causes a major scene when Kinsan declares his intentions toward Tsukushi! Still desperate for money, Tsukushi goes to Tsukasa who comes up with a plan that everyone can benefit from. That is, if Tsukushi can win a beauty contest...!
2005-01-01|2005-12-30.name: Vol. 10

2005-01-01|2005-12-30.description:
His sakabatô broken in battle, Kenshin seeks out the man who forged it - Arai Shakku - only to be turned away. Seiku, son of the legendary swordsmith, had for a time been continuing his father's work (the forging of katana, meant for killing), but has since given up that calling and spends his time making humble cooking knives. Respecting Seiku's ishes, Kenshin leaven without the desired blade... but notbefore Shishio's spies learn that Shakku has forged one last sword. Meanwhile, Shishio arrives in Kyoto with orders for his ten generals or "Ten Swords" to join him and put into motion a plan to take over Japan. Chô, one of Shishio's "swords," learns early of Shakku's final blade and determines to secure it at any cost. Now, armed only with his broken sakabatô, Kenshin must face Chô in battle...

2005-01-01|2005-12-30.description:
Fame, honor, and respect come with knighthood--but at what cost? Kok-Jung has been requested by Merlin to accompany him on a dragon hunt to capture Siegfried's Dragon. Merlin has some dark secrets and ulterior motives that only Beul-Hee knows about...but will she get the chance to tell Kok-Jung? Also, what exactly is the Wiseman's Stone and what power does it hold? Only Merlin knows, but his lips are sealed...

Back Blurb

Fame, honor, and respect come with knighthood but -- for a Korean knight in King Arthur's court -- mystery, intrigue, and betrayal are also part of the job.

Things seem simple enough when Merlin asks Kok-Jung to help capture Siegfriend's dragon... but Kok-Jung's shaman Beul-Hee knows Merlin has dark secret and ulterior motives. Can Beul-Hee warn Kok-Jung in time? If she can't, will the headstrong, young dragon hunter survive a battle with an enraged army of Camelot's knights?

2005-01-01|2005-12-30.description:
Shuichi returns to Japan and to his surprise, Eiri has come to greet him at the airport. Shuichi reveals that he just wants Eiri to open up to him. Hearing this, Eiri offers to say "I love you"...if Shuichi agrees to pay him every time he says it. Although Eiri is joking, Shuichi is dead serious about raising the money to hear those precious words. However, Eiri says something else that will leave Shuichi so shocked he will be unable to sing!

Track 42 - 45 & bonus track.

In this, the final volume of Pet Shop of Horrors, the sinister saga of Count D and Leon Orcot comes to its chilling conclusion.

DEPARTURE: When two you ladies pay a visit to Count D's shop, they're not looking to take home a pet, but their little brother -- Chris Orcot!

DISAPPEARANCE: Count D has disappeared, and the hunt to find him is on, especially since a new serial killer has emerged, one whose modus operandi appears to involve frenzied wild animals.

DUPLICATION: When Detective Orcot meets Count D's father, it becomes clear that the apple doesn't fall far from the tree.

D: In the climactic final chapter of Pet Shop of Horrors the truth about Count D and his family revealed... and we say good-bye to a few old friends.

As Earth is anesthetized by Planet Anesthesia, the only mobile people left are the members of Keron Forces and those close to Keroro. One by one, Keroro Platoon members are silenced and their friends are eliminated! Natsumi tries to defend Earth but is foiled by Tororo. With the help of Kûkaku--a one-armed explosives expert and old friend of the mysterious talking cat Yoruichi--Ichigo and crew are one step closer to infiltrating the Soul Society and rescuing their friend Rukia before she is executed. For Kûkaku's plan to work, Ichigo must control his enormous reservoir of spiritual energy--and there's no telling how much collateral damage this will cause. Nos deux tourtereaux sont en pleins ébats sexuels. Bien que ce ne soit pas dans ses habitudes d’éjaculateur précoce, Makoto a beau faire, a beau s’acharner, il n’y arrive pas… Ça ne vient pas. Rien de bien grave, me direz-vous, ce sont des choses qui arrivent… Oui, mais c’est oublier que nos héros ont la fâcheuse tendance de se faire des montagnes de petits riens. Et, évidemment, Makoto s’imagine déjà souffrant d’anéjaculation et, de son côté, Yura se demande si son vagin ne se serait pas élargi… Est-elle toujours désirable ?

2005-01-01|2005-12-30.description: It's all-out family warfare now that Ryoki's mother has dished some serious dirt about big brother Shinogu's past, resulting in Hatsumi's heavenly bro leaving on bad terms. Hoping to dissuade him from forever severing his ties with the Narita household, Hatsumi swings by Shinogu's pad, but not before dropping in on Ryoki and totally making his day (that is, until he finds out that she's still talking to her bro, and you know how he feels aboutthat). Infuriated that Hatsumi still has the audacity to even think of any man but his wonderful self, Ryoki demands that Hatsumi choose between him and Shinogu. Hatsumi's about to get all wishy-washy--big surprise there--but Ryoki comes up with the perfect way to solidify their relationship...by running off to Izu together!

2005-01-01|2005-12-30.description:
Content

Sign 'O' The Times - Muddling moron, or master of a million chess games? More than just a Time Lord? Mystical magician? Merlin? Philip MacDonald examines the character of the Seventh Doctor ...

The Seventh Doctor on TV

SEASON 24:

In Production - Andrew Pixley finds trouble in the TARDIS, as the colours of the Sixth Doctor are discarded, and we encounter the secretive Seventh ...

The Stories - In which there's Loyhargil on Lakertya, a parasite in paradise, shenanigans at Shangri-La and frostbite at the freezer centre ...

SEASON 25:

In Production - The Doctor celebrated his 25th birthday in 1988, but would anyone notice? Perhaps the Daleks and the Cybermen could save the day?

The Stories - In which there's Terror at Totter's Lane, unhappiness underground, weirdos at Windsor and psychos at the circus ...

SEASON 26:

In Production - It was almost the end of the road for the Doctor and Ace - but first there was some work to do!

The Stories - In which there's commotion in Carbury, husks in the house, bloodsuckers on the beach and pussies in Perivale ...

Further Adventures

Seventh Doctor Audios - Dave Owen listens in to the audio adventures of the Seventh Doctor, Mel, Ace, Bernice and Hex ...

Seventh Doctor Books - Matt Michael discovers what happened after Survival, as he works his way through the New Adventures ...

Seventh Doctor Comics - Jonny Morris leafs through his old DWMs to consider the Seventh Doctor's adventures in the strip ...

Errata - Andrew Pixley puts right what once went wrong!

Afterword - Sophie Aldred reflects on her time on the series ...

Rookie firefighter Daigo Asahina will go to extraordinary lengths to save lives, but his latest unauthorized rescue method may get him fired! Insisting to his supervisors that he did the right thing, Daigo resigns himself to his fate and hangs up his firefighting gear. Then, on a dinner date with his former high school teacher (and object of his affections), a blackout traps them in a glass elevator high above the city, and things go from bad to worse...
